#: ../../T/Troll-O-Meter.rst:5
msgid "Troll-O-Meter"
msgstr "Troll-O-Meter"

#: ../../T/Troll-O-Meter.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../T/Troll-O-Meter.rst:9
msgid ""
"Common Usenet jargon for a notional instrument used to measure the "
"provocation level of a Usenet :ref:`troll`\\. \"Come on, everyone! If the "
"above doesn't set off the Troll-O-Meter, we're going to have to get him to "
"run around with a big blinking sign saying ‘I am a troll, I’m only in it for"
" the controversy and flames', and shooting random gobs of Jell-O(tm) at us "
"before the point is proven.\" Mentions of the Troll-O-Meter are often "
"accompanied by an ASCII picture of an arrow pointing at a numeric scale. "
"Compare :ref:`bogometer`\\, :ref:`Indent-o-Meter`\\."
msgstr ""
"Usenetの\\ :ref:`troll`\\ "
"の挑発レベルを測定するための想像上の計器を指す、よくあるUsenetジャーゴン。「さあみんな!上の投稿がTroll-O-"
"Meterを作動させないなら、彼に‘私はトロールだ、論争と炎上のためだけにここにいる’と書かれた大きな点滅看板を持って走り回らせ、論点が証明される前に我々にJell-O(tm)の塊をランダムに投げつけさせるしかないな」。Troll-"
"O-Meterへの言及には、数値目盛りを指す矢印のASCIIの絵がしばしば添えられる。\\ :ref:`bogometer`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`Indent-o-Meter`\\ と比較せよ。"
